source: crates/pi-doctor-cli/tests/milestone4_gpio.rs
expression: "pi_doctor::doctor::gpio::render(&ctx)"
---
pi-doctor doctor gpio
GPIO stack recommendation
  gpiochip devices: gpiochip0, gpiochip4
  pinctrl: present
  libgpiod tools: gpioinfo, gpiodetect
  raspi-gpio: present (deprecated)

Recommended path
  Use pinctrl for Raspberry Pi-specific hardware-state inspection and alternate-function visibility.
  Use libgpiod tools for generic Linux GPIO line ownership and userspace line work.

Potential conflicts
  Overlay `spi0-1cs` likely enables a bus or peripheral already.
  GPIO3 currently appears owned by alternate function SDA1.
  GPIO18 currently appears owned by alternate function PWM0_CHAN2.
